column2: Date: 2/14/18, 1:30-2:20 pm Class: Tutorial CE Instructor: Dake Zhou, Alex Chang No. Students: 17 Arranged how? Tutorial

Notes: Work and Conservation of Energy, pg 31-35. Homework, same topic, problems 3-4. Exam next Thursday, 2/22, emphasis on relative motion, forces, and newtons laws. Students in groups of 4-5, working individually/ together from booklet. Class has one main TA and one grader- grader hands back papers for the first few minutes of class, then joins as regular TA. O- at least one group is not talking to each other the entire time. Only marking SQ when student raises their hand, not questions during 1o1 discussion. TA is 5 minutes late. 2 groups of 4, 3 groups of 3.
